bug.short_desc: codeSelect does not work in all cases.

long_desc.thetext:
Build ID: I20071213-1700
Steps To Reproduce: It does work for me in some cases (mostly with JDK API).
More information: It does work for me in some cases (mostly with JDK API). e.g. of a case that does not work: private transient BalancerController controller = new TimeBasedBalancerController(); standing (can invoking show hierarchy) on BalancerController (interface) does not show any implementation, but doing the same on the implementation shows it correctly.
Anything in .log? What happens if you use F4 (Open Type Hierarchy)?
Nothing in the log. F4 (Open Type Hierarchy) suffers from the same issue.
Can you provide us with a test case that we can reproduce? Unfortunately it works when we try it here on latest 3.4 and 3.3.2 builds and hence can't do much until we have can reproduce it here.

OK, I think I got your use case:
It works when the caret is inside an identifier but not when it is inside a method/constructor call i.e. F4/Ctrl+T
Works: MyCl<caret>ass new MyCl<caret>ass()
Does not work: new MyClass(<caret>) new MyClass(/* test1 */ <caret> /* test1 */)
This behavior is true for all element based actions (e.g. F3) and caused by the implementation if org.eclipse.jdt.core.ICodeAssist.codeSelect(int, int) which only looks at identifiers.
Moving to JDT Core. Either org.eclipse.jdt.core.ICodeAssist.codeSelect(int, int) should be improved to handle these cases or a new variant is needed. Otherwise we can't do much.
